{
    "name": "Bogeyman",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Bogeyman",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 79",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 79",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrd?"
                    },
                    "page": 79
                }
            ],
            "html": "These nocturnal stalkers tail their chosen quarry for days, even weeks at a time, ominously showing up in back alleys, shadowy street corners, and even in victims\u2019 own homes before going in for the kill. For unfathomable reasons, a bogeyman may spare a victim\u2019s life and instead kidnap them, absconding to a far-off location before returning years later with a fresh bogey in tow.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Fey</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 29"
        },
        {
            "name": "Bogeyman",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Bogey Origins",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                                "alt": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrd?"
                            },
                            "page": 78
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "While bogeymen stem from bugaboos and bugaboos from bogeys, it is unknown where, exactly, bogeys come from. If superstitious storytellers are to be believed, then bogeys arise from the unfortunate victims kidnapped by bogeymen. According to these tales, victims go missing for months or even years before returning as bogeys to the town they once called home."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Epidemic of Terror",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                                "alt": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrd?"
                            },
                            "page": 78
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Locations",
                        "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Bogeymen and their lesser kin delight in instilling fear in small communities where gossip can quickly amplify their shadowy deeds. In such locales, bogeymen use peoples\u2019 natural tendency to spread misinformation to sow discord and escape notice\u2014for who would rightfully believe that an actual bogeyman is behind the latest murder?"
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 78",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrd?"
                    },
                    "page": 78
                }
            ],
            "html": "Bogeymen are stealers of innocence and devourers of souls. Few targets who survive an encounter with them remain unchanged. Different names are given to bogeymen according to their varying sizes and degrees of power, which typically advance as the monsters consume more souls."
        }
    ],
